Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Mix together granola, flour, brown sugar, shortening, white sugar, egg, salt, vanilla extract and baking soda together in a medium size mixing bowl. Mix until well blended. Drop by teaspoonfuls 1 1/2 inches apart on baking sheets. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown. Cool on wire racks.